ENVIRONMENTAL OPPORTUNITY ADJUSTMENT RULE

Tier 1 — Elite Environment:

* strongest continuation assumptions
* strongest persistence assumptions
* strongest asymmetry durability
* strongest liquidity support
* strongest execution durability

Tier 2 — Strong Environment:

* favorable continuation conditions
* moderate-to-strong persistence assumptions
* manageable fragility conditions

Tier 3 — Moderate Environment:

* mixed continuation quality
* reduced persistence assumptions
* elevated volatility sensitivity
* elevated compression sensitivity
* elevated adaptation requirements

Tier 4 — Fragile Environment:

* deteriorating continuation quality
* elevated liquidity fragility
* elevated asymmetry deterioration
* elevated execution instability
* elevated nonlinear-event sensitivity

Tier 5 — Dangerous Environment:

* highly unstable continuation conditions
* elevated systemic instability
* elevated contagion sensitivity
* elevated volatility instability
* elevated liquidity deterioration probability

